        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 5:12PM EDT by NWS Indianapolis IN</headline>
        <description>At 512 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Newport, or 17 miles southeast of Danville, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crawfordsville, Covington, Veedersburg, Newport, Cayuga, Montezuma,
Waynetown, New Market, Dana, Hillsboro, Kingman, Perrysville,
Bloomingdale, Marshall, Wingate, Newtown, Mellott, Wallace, Alamo,
and Lodi.

This includes Interstate 74 between mile markers 1 and 29.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
